description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust provides acute and community health services to people living in the Wakefield and North Kirklees districts of West Yorkshire.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Procurement Department have an opportunity for a forward thinking, proactive and enthusiastic Contracting Manager to join the team to provide contract advice and expertise on public procurement and NHS procurement policy. To manage a portfolio of contracts, and be responsible for all sourcing, tendering and contractual activity to select and appoint suppliers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work closely with user departments, usually as part of a multi-disciplinary team, in order to understand their needs and interpret these through to the appropriate contractual agreements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an excellent opportunity to work as part of dynamic team undertaking a professional contracting role across a broad range of goods and services. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
